featured_reviews.review_id:
This masjid is in existence since late 1970s. The foundation is laid by Syed Mujtaba Ashraf(Kichaucha Shareef). The masjid is still under construction on its designing part otherwise the internal area is fully furbished. Ashraful masajid is regarded as the biggest mosque in North Bengal  in terms of area and accomodation, so don't worry about parking and Wuzu. The Jumaah Prayer Khutba commence at 1pm and Eid Namaz held between 8:30 - 9:00 am. Every festival and Niyaz of Aulia is celebrated with great enthusiasm and respect. The committee member used to take out procession on 12th Rabi ul Awal and special food or sweets is distributed throughout the area as for the Niyaz of Aulia e Ikram also.
People of Ashraf Nagar is very fateful that their Imam is very pious and steadfast in the Deen of Islam, he is very soft-hearted towards the right people and a naked sword who speaks blasphemy about the deen. Everybody must visit this place it's a very beautiful place to live in where people share common opinion and respect each other views.

Masjid al-Haram

Makkah Masjid or Mecca Masjid, is a congregational mosque in Hyderabad, India. It is one of the largest mosques in India with a capacity of 10,000 people.[2] The mosque was built during the 17th century, and is a state-protected monument. It serves as the primary mosque for the Old City of Hyderabad,[3] and is located close to the historic landmarks of Charminar, Chowmahalla Palace and Laad Bazaar.

featured_reviews.review_id:
The serene atmosphere, beautiful architecture, and the warm welcome from the community made my visit memorable.

The mosque's intricate design and well-maintained premises reflect the care and dedication of those who oversee it. The prayer hall was spacious and immaculately clean, providing a peaceful place for worship and reflection.

The congregation was friendly and welcoming, making me feel like a part of the community, even though I was just a visitor. I appreciated the opportunity to learn more about Islamic culture and traditions during my visit.

Overall, this mosque is a symbol of unity and spirituality. Whether you're a member of the Muslim community or a curious visitor like myself, I highly recommend visiting this place of worship. It's a testament to the beauty of diversity and the importance of understanding and respect among different faiths.

#Mosque #Peaceful #Unity
